i am building a hotel management system with php mysql for my client a final year student. 

Core Modules and Features
Specify which functionalities your client requires for their final year project. Common modules include:

1. User Management: Roles like Admin (full control), Receptionist (bookings/check-ins), and Customer (viewing rooms)Room Management: Categories (Single, Deluxe, Suite), pricing, and real-time availability

2. Room Management: Categories (Single, Deluxe, Suite), pricing, and real-time availability 

3. Booking System: Online reservations, date range selection, and status tracking (Pending, Confirmed, Cancelled) 

4. Billing & Payments: Automated invoice generation and payment method tracking (Cash, Card, UPI)

5. Guest Records: Storing names, contact info, and ID proof for security

6. Reporting: Occupancy rates, revenue, and guest statistics

Database Design

Create an Entity-Relationship Diagram (ERD) and the corresponding SQL schema. Key tables include:

1. Users (user_id, username, password (hashed), role)

2. Rooms (room_id, room_type, price_per_night, status (Available/Occupied).)

3. Bookings (booking_id, user_id, room_id, check_in, check_out, total_amount)

4. Payments (payment_id, booking_id, amount, payment_status)

NOTE: all database table has to have createdAt and updatedAt columns

Technology Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript (or a framework like React/Vue if preferred) // which one is best? 


Backend: PHP

Database: MySQL

Security Considerations
Implement proper authentication, authorization, and protection against common vulnerabilities like SQL injection and XSS.